<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--DeadHeat     11-18 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Dead Heat,0149</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Jockeys Won't Be Flogging A Dead Horse After All</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   According to the official horseracing guides, We're
in the Money and English River don't stand much chance of winning
their races today. They're listed as dead.
   But the ghostly form of We're in the Money, mistakenly declared
dead three days ago, will line up at Ascot. English River, whose
death was announced by the official form book after a fall last
season, will run at Nottingham.
   Graham Roe, who trains We're in the Money, said another trainer's
secretary had confused the filly with another horse to cause the
mixup.
   ``But it was a nasty three or four hours before I found out she
was all right,'' Roe said. ``The filly is most definitely alive and
runs (today).''
   Bettors are wondering whether either horse will figure in a dead
heat.
</TEXT>
