<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0441</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Snow Piles Up In Western Mountain Regions</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   More than a foot of snow piled up in Colorado, Utah and Nevada
early today, and strong winds accompanying the storm system howled
through the Southwest.
   Two-foot drifts blown by strong winds were measured near Austin,
Nev. Gusts reached 39 mph at Daggett, Calif.
   Showers were scattered in southeast Texas and eastern Florida.
   Snowfall was generally light this morning in the northern Rockies
and parts of the northern Plains.
   Snow accumulations in the Colorado Rockies reached more than 12
inches. A warning for heavy snow was in effect for the state's
mountain areas. In Utah, a few inches fell in the valleys and up to
14 inches at the Alta and Sundance ski resorts.
   Today's forecast: snow over the northern and central Rockies,
South Dakota and western Nebraska; scattered showers and
thunderstorms for parts of the central Plains and the middle and
lower Mississippi Valley.
   Temperatures should be 10 to 20 degrees colder than normal from
the Rockies across western parts of the Dakotas and western
Nebraska. Highs should be in the 20s from northern Minnesota to the
northern Rockies; in the 30s and 40s from the northern half of New
England through New York state, the Great Lakes, Iowa, Missouri,
Nebraska, Kansas and the central and southern Rockies, and the
northern Pacific coast.
   Temperatures should reach the 70s from southern South Carolina
across northern Florida and the Gulf Coast to eastern and
south-central Texas. Highs should be near 80 degrees in southern
Texas and in the 80s in Florida; the 50s and 60s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 6
degrees at Glasgow, Mont., to 80 degrees at Homestead (Fla.) Air
Force Base.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 42 fair; Boston 38 fair; Buffalo 37 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 55 fair; Cincinnati 34 fair; Cleveland 31 partly
cloudy; Detroit 31 fair; Miami 77 fair; New York 42 fair;
Philadelphia 37 fair; Pittsburgh 32 fair; Portland, Maine 36 fair;
Washington 43 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 16 snow; Chicago 37 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 57
cloudy; Denver 31 partly cloudy; Des Moines 43 cloudy; Indianapolis
35 partly cloudy; Kansas City 48 partly cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul
21 cloudy; Nashville 34 fair; New Orleans 57 fair; St. Louis 40
cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 35 fair; Anchorage 16 fair; Las Vegas 48
windy; Los Angeles 57 windy; Phoenix 54 fair; Salt Lake City 33
snow; San Diego 57 fair; San Francisco 49 fair; Seattle 40 foggy.
   _Canada: Montreal 37 windy; Toronto 32 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
