<HEAD>With PM-Bush Rdp</HEAD>
<HEAD>Bush Meets with Governors</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President-elect George Bush met 18
governors and governors-elect today because, he said, ``I wanted to
send an early signal to the governors and the states of my interests
in working with the governors, Democrats and Republicans alike.''
   He called the session both ``productive'' and also ``symbolic.''
   Bush, meeting briefly with reporters after the morning meeting,
said he hoped that rather than having the federal government mandate
programs that require state spending ``I'd like to have it the other
way around'' with the federal government responsive to the state
needs.
   He also said that his selection of retiring New Hampshire Gov.
John Sununu as chief of staff ``sends that same signal of my
interest in having strong input from the governors.''
   The president-elect said he wants to meet with the governors
early and address the issues of environment and education.
   Virginia Gov. Gerald Baliles, host of the conference, said the
governors had had a ``full, friendly and free discussion'' with Bush
on issues that included the deficit.
   ``The vice president asked for the governors' help and he'll get
it,'' Baliles said.
