<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Madonna's Dress,0173</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dancer In South Carolina Arrested In Theft Of Madonna's Dress</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NOVI, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A topless dancer has been arrested in a crime
of fashion _ stealing a dress valued at $20,000 that belonged to pop
star Madonna.
   The 19-year-old woman was arrested Thursday in Myrtle Beach,
S.C., where she had been working for a few weeks, police said.
   The strapless blue number worn by the singer during the song
``True Blue'' in the movie ``Who's that Girl?'' was stolen July 15
from a display of rock memorabilia at a mall in Novi, a Detroit
suburb. Madonna is from nearby Rochester.
   Three days later, four teen-agers turned the dress in, saying
they found it. Later, two of them told officers who they thought
stole the dress. Detective Ralph Fluhart said he had been tracking
the woman since then.
   The woman, who has not yet been charged in Michigan, faces a
charge of felony larceny, which carries up to five years in prison
and a $2,500 fine.
</TEXT>
