<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Turkeys,0122</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Wreck Releases Turkeys On Highway</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUSTIN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hundreds of turkeys got at least a temporary
pre-Thanksgiving reprieve when a tractor-trailer carrying them to
slaughter rolled over after a collision.
   Some of the 2,500 white, medium-sized turkeys were killed
Thursday, but others were freed from their cages and strutted
around, tying up traffic on Interstate 35 for more than three hours.
   No people were injured in the collision between the truck and a
car, said Edwin Anderson, an emergency medical technician.
   Beth Baumann of the Humane Society of Austin said the turkeys
would be kept in shelters for Plantation Foods company of Waco, and
would be given away if the company no longer wanted them.
</TEXT>
