<1ST_LINE>r p AM-BRF--MayoralElection     11-18 0162</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Mayoral Election,0165</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Houston Mayor Kathy Whitmire Says Tells Group She Will Run Again</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mayor Kathy Whitmire, serving her fourth term as
leader of the nation's fourth-largest city, says she is planning to
run for re-election in 1989.
   Mrs. Whitmire reportedly mentioned her intention Thursday in an
off-hand remark at the organizational meeting of the Houston
Breakfast Leadership Forum.
   ```By the way, if anyone is wondering, I do intend to run for
re-election,''' Cindy Clifford, one of the organizers, quoted the
mayor as saying.
   Asked Thursday night to confirm the report, Mrs. Whitmire said:
``I'm not starting a campaign tonight or making an announcement of
campaign plans today. It's no secret, and it hasn't been, that I
have no plans to quit at the end of this term and have been planning
to seek another term if the voters allow me to do that.''
   Former Mayor Fred Hofheinz has said he is considering a mayoral
race next year.
</TEXT>
