<HEAD>US-Soviet Medical Research Agreement Signed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Top health officials of the U.S. and Soviet
Union signed an agreement Friday in Moscow expanding areas of
cooperation in medical research, it was announced here.
   The so-called summary memorandum recognizes 11 scientific
research areas, including three new ones added this year: use of
non-human primates such as baboons and monkeys; alcohol and drug
abuse and AIDS.
   The U.S. delegation was headed by Dr. Robert E. Windom, assistant
secretary for health at the Department of Health and Human Services.
