<HEAD>New Bureau Chief for Northern New England</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CONCORD, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Larry Laughlin, news editor for The
Associated Press in Richmond, Va., has been named the AP's chief of
bureau for northern New England, AP President Louis D. Boccardi
announced Friday.
   Laughlin, 40, will direct the AP's news and marketing operations
in Maine, Vermont and New Hampshire, based in Concord. He succeeds
Jonathan Kellogg, who resigned to become managing editor of the
Portland (Maine) Press Herald and Maine Sunday Telegram.
   Laughlin joined the AP in Boston in 1976. He transferred to
Providence, R.I., in 1978 and was named correspondent there the
following year. He became Richmond news editor in 1982.
   Laughlin is a native of Taunton, Mass., and began his journalism
career at the Taunton Daily Gazette. He is a graduate of Providence
College.
