<HEAD>London Stocks Down 1.4 Points</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were little changed Friday after the
government reported inflation rose 0.5 percent in October.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was down 1.4
points, or 0.08 percent, at 1,822.2 at midday.
   Volume was moderate and 360.5 million shares changed hands,
compared with 280.2 million at the same time Thursday.
   Trading began on a positive note, helped by steady performances
in overseas stock and foreign exchange markets.
   Persistent weakness in the dollar despite concerted intervention
by central banks has reawakened worries about the course of interest
rates, both in the United States and in Britain, dealers said.
   Traders were relieved by the government's report showing
Britain's inflation rose to an annual rate of 6.4 percent in October
from 5.9 percent in September, dealers said. The market had expected
an increase of that magnitude.
