   On Thursday, central banks of the industrialized countries began
what appeared to be a concerted effort to intervene in foreign
exchange markets to support the slumping dollar.
   That intervention continued today, pushing the U.S. currency
higher.
   But analysts said many traders were waiting skeptically to see
whether the dollar could manage a sustained period of recovery on
its own.
   They also said market participants still had many misgivings
about the outlook for interest rates. A Treasury auction of 30-year
bonds on Thursday met with a relatively cool response.
   RJR Nabisco rose 1| to 84]. The company was expected to receive
formal offers late today from competing groups seeking to acquire
its stock.
   Veeco Instruments added | to 25] on top of a 1~-point gain
Thursday, when the company agreed to be acquired by Unitech PLC for
$26.50 a share.
