<HEAD>Corn, Soybeans Close Lower; Wheat Advances</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Corn and soybean futures closed modestly lower
while most wheat futures advanced slightly in subdued trading Friday
on the Chicago Board of Trade.
   With little fresh news to move the markets, corn and soybean
prices drifted lower, analysts said. The contract for November
delivery of soybeans expired at noon CST at $7.27} a bushel, 8\
cents above Thursday's final price.
   Wheat gained on light support from commercial buyers. Speculative
buying of wheat futures also increased on the theory that wheat's
resistance to downward pressure from the neighboring pits during the
past week indicated good underlying strength in the wheat market,
analysts said.
   At the close, wheat was { cent lower to 1} cents higher with the
contract for delivery in December at $4.11 a bushel; corn was { cent
to 2\ cents lower with December at $2.58 a bushel; oats were { cent
to 3{ cents lower with December at $2.00{ a bushel; and soybeans
were 2 cents to 6{ cents lower with January at $7.32 a bushel.
